WITH Barcelona reportedly set to make financial cuts on their wage bill, Gabonese star Pierre- Emerick Aubameyang is said to be exempted from the club’s money crisis. To ease the club’s woes, Barcelona are reportedly set to reduce its hefty wage bill which is said to be around £476 million. According to the Mirror, the Spanish giants want to slash their wage structure by £136 million.   Troost-Ekong ruled out of Sao Tomé & Principe clash     Frenkie de Jong: Man United reach agreement with Barcelona     Zidane close to joining PSG as manager   According to the UK-based publication, players such as Samuel Umitit, Miralem Panic, Riqui Puig, Oscar Mingueza, and Clement Lenglet have been told that they are ‘surplus to requirements. However, Barca players Ferran Torres, Pedri, Ansu Fati, Ronald Araujo, and also Aubameyang, will be left out of the new financial restructuring proceedings. The report also mentioned that Gerrard Pique, Sergio Busquets, Jordi Alba, and Sergi Roberto are crucial to the club’s immediate financial plans.